            <person xml:id="pers1380">
               <p>Mason, a native of <placeName>Hampshire</placeName>, was admitted on trial as an
                     <seg ana="itinerancy">itinerant preacher</seg> in <date when="1764">1764</date>
                  and in full status in <date when="1765">1765</date> (see <hi rend="italic"
                     >Works</hi>, 10:303). He was soon serving as an Assistant and became one of
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s frequent
                  correspondents. Health issues led him to desist travelling in <date when="1797"
                     >1797</date> and settle near <placeName>Portsmouth</placeName>. See <hi
                     rend="italic">EMP</hi>, 3:307–15; and <hi rend="italic">Minutes</hi>
                  (post-Wesley, <date when="1810">1810</date>), 3:134–35.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
